h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://justinmeiners.github.io/neural-nets-sim/\">McCulloch &#x26; Pitts Neural Net Simulator</a> - Simulator for a historical computational model based on neurons.</li>","updatedAt":"2019-02-14T03:37:21.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Programming</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jefferis/nat\">nat: NeuroAnatomy Toolbox</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/jefferis/nat\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">47</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":47,\"repo\":\"jefferis/nat\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Package for the (3D) visualisation and analysis of biological image data, especially tracings of single neurons.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-30T19:15:57.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Programming</h2><h3>R</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/cwatson/brainGraph\">brainGraph</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/cwatson/brainGraph\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">104</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":104,\"repo\":\"cwatson/brainGraph\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Package for performing graph theory analyses of brain MRI data.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-30T19:14:44.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Newsletters</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.tnb.ua.ac.be/mailman/listinfo/comp-neuro\">Comp-neuro</a> - A mailing list that is is intended to address the broad range of research approaches and issues involved in the general field of computational neuroscience.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-30T19:07:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Ebooks</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://neuronaldynamics.epfl.ch\">Neuronal Dynamics</a> - Open-access electronic textbook that covers computational and theoretical neuroscience. Provided by École Polytechnique Fédérale de Lausanne (EPFL).</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-30T19:01:57.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Miscellaneous</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/awesomedata/awesome-public-datasets#neuroscience\">Awesome Public Datasets - Neuroscience</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/awesomedata/awesome-public-datasets#neuroscience\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">44.4k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":44353,\"repo\":\"awesomedata/awesome-public-datasets\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - High-quality open neuroscience datasets.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-30T18:51:35.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Communities</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://psychology.stackexchange.com\">StackExchange</a> - Psychology and neuroscience StackExchange site.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-10-30T18:47:11.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Miscellaneous</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://senselab.med.yale.edu/NeuronDB\">NeuronDB</a> - Searchable database for  of three types of neuronal properties: voltage gated conductances, neurotransmitter receptors, and neurotransmitter substances.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-06-03T04:50:17.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Communities</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.quora.com/topic/Neuroscience-1\">Quora</a> - Neuroscience topic on Quora contains answers, often by experts, to questions ranging from basic to advanced.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-07T05:04:13.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Communities</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/ScienceNetwork/comments/ptye0/link_tables/\">Reddit</a> - List of neuroscience, psychology and cognitive science subreddits.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-07-07T05:04:13.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Ebooks</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://grey.colorado.edu/CompCogNeuro/index.php/CCNBook/Main\">Computational Cognitive Neuroscience</a> - Text which provides an in-depth introduction to the main ideas in the computational cognitive neuroscience, a field which aims to understand the brain by using biologically based computational models.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-06-26T19:28:51.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Miscellaneous</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://senselab.med.yale.edu/ModelDB/default.cshtml\">ModelDB</a> - Searchable database for computational neuroscience models.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-06-26T19:28:51.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Ebooks</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://nba.uth.tmc.edu/neuroscience/m/index.htm\">Neuroscience Online</a> - Open-access electronic textbook and interactive courseware covering neuroscience in depth. Provided by the Department of Neurobiology and Anantomy at the University of Texas Medical School at Houston.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-06-20T05:59:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Miscellaneous</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://learn-anything.xyz/neuroscience\">Neuroscience Mindmap</a> - Interactive mindmap containing curated resources for anyone interested in learning neuroscience.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-06-20T05:59:56.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Programming</h2><h3>C++</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/BlueBrain/Brayns\">Brayns</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/BlueBrain/Brayns\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">239</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":239,\"repo\":\"BlueBrain/Brayns\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Minimalistic visualiser that can perform ray-traced rendering of neurons. Ray-tracing can help to highlight areas of neural circuits where cells touch each other and where synapses are being created leading to a better understanding of how individual cells and subsequently the brain functions.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-06-14T14:26:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Programming</h2><h3>JavaScript</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/aces/brainbrowser\">Brainbrowser</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/aces/brainbrowser\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">281</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":281,\"repo\":\"aces/brainbrowser\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Library exposing set of web-based 3D visualization tools primarily targetting neuroimaging.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-06-14T14:26:40.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Programming</h2><h3>Python</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/brian-team/brian2\">Brian2</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/brian-team/brian2\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">548</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":548,\"repo\":\"brian-team/brian2\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Free, open source simulator for spiking neural networks.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-06-10T15:13:34.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Blogs</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://blogs.scientificamerican.com/scicurious-brain/\">The scicurious brain</a> - Maintained by <a href=\"https://blogs.scientificamerican.com/\">Scientific American</a>, this blog typically covers one research paper in a single entry.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-18T04:14:34.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>Blogs</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://blogs.nature.com/actionpotential\">Action Potential</a> - Forum operated by neuroscience editors at the journal, Nature.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-18T04:14:34.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>MOOCs</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.mcb80x.org/\">The Fundamentals of Neuroscience | Harvard &#x26; edX</a> - Serves an introductory survery of topics in neuroscience and has no specific prerequisites, though some prior exposure to biology and/or chemistry can be helpful.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-18T04:14:34.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>MOOCs</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.coursera.org/learn/computational-neuroscience\">Computational Neuroscience | Coursera</a> - Provides an introduction to basic computational methods for understanding what nervous systems do and for determining how they function.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-18T04:14:34.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Resources</h2><h3>MOOCs</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.coursera.org/learn/medical-neuroscience\">Medical Neuroscience</a> - Explores the functional organization and neurophysiology of the human central nervous system, while providing a neurobiological framework for understanding human behavior.</li>","updatedAt":"2017-05-18T04:14:34.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Programming</h2><h3>Python</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/nilearn/nilearn\">Nilearn</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/nilearn/nilearn\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">741</span></s